data.description: HIGHEST AND BEST BY 8 PM MONDAY FEB 26TH You still can submit offers today. One of Claremont's gems! This beautiful 3 bedroom, 2 1/2 bath home has had the exterior freshly painted, the beautiful, oak, hardwoods refinished and the lovely kitchen updated with new hardware, new quartz countertops and new tile backsplash. It has a  daylight basement and overlooks the ponds out back! Enter into the 2 story foyer through a gorgeous, leaded glass door. There is a flex space to the left which would make a great office, formal dining room or living room...maybe a playroom for the kids! The newly refreshed kitchen has a lovely eating area with a doorwall that leads to a composite deck, overlooking the large backyard and 2 ponds. The kitchen/eating area is open to the great room with impressive vaulted ceilings and a warm, gas fireplace. Down the hall you will find a wonderful primary ensuite complete with trayed ceilings, a large bathroom with jetted tub, separate shower, private toilet area and an ample walk in closet. The laundry room is conveniently off of the garage on the main floor and has a laundry tub to wash up in when coming inside. There is a 1/2 bath near the garage entrance also. Upstairs there are 2 large bedrooms, separated by a catwalk that overlooks the lower level, and a full bath. The daylight basement can be accessed through the laundry room. The rec room area is extremely large and bathed in natural sunlight coming from the 4 large windows that overlook the backyard. There is also plenty of storage, a large workshop and its even studded for another bath, if desired. Outside you have a 2nd story deck with lights built in. Its also wired for a hot tub. There is a storage area below the deck so you can keep the garage tidy. Off of the deck is a beautiful paver patio. Nice landscaping w/ gorgeous perennials.  What a great home to entertain in! The sub includes park areas and access to the metropark behind it. Easy access to I-275. Huron Schools!
